# Fintech GA4 Customer Survival Analysis (BigQuery & BQML)

## Business Case
Series A/B fintech startups face highly volatile deposit habits. Traditional binary churn models (logistic regression) fail because they cannot account for "censored data"—users who are slowing down their deposit velocity but haven't officially closed their accounts yet. 

This project builds a **Cox Proportional Hazards Model natively within Google BigQuery (BQML)** using raw, nested Google Analytics 4 clickstream data. It predicts the *time-to-event velocity of deposit deceleration*, allowing growth teams to calculate accurate Customer Lifetime Value (LTV) and protect startup runway.

## Data Infrastructure Architecture
1. **Flattening Layer:** Unpacks nested GA4 event parameters and user arrays using SQL `UNNEST()`.
2. **Sessionization Layer:** Stitches user clickstreams into chronological product sessions.
3. **Feature Store Matrix:** Engineers categorical and numerical customer covariates (e.g., login frequency, average deposit size, KYC status).
4. **Predictive Modeling:** Trains a cloud-native `COX_PH` survival engine to output hazard ratios for investor dashboards.
